        <mj-text align="left" font-size="20px" color="grey"><h1>How to test</h1></mj-text>
        <mj-text align="left" color="grey"><p>In order to execute this program, install the dependencies on
 <code>requiriments.txt</code> and run the next command:</p>

<p><code>python md2html.py readme.md test_files/test_03/template.mjml &gt; readme.mjml</code></p>

<p>Yes. This readme is formatted and can be prettified by this tool ;-)</p>

<p>After that, you will have a fully functional mjml file that can be
 converted into html.</p></mj-text>
